{
  "texts": [
    "We attribute the slow sampling of the diffusion model-based SISR method to the Gaussian distribution adopted in the denoising distribution and propose to employ a complex multimodal distribution to model Random SR (8×) samples generated by SRDDGAN using latent variable Z.",
    "Our method generates diverse predicted SR images, including differences in facial attributes and hair (e.g., the second hair detail has a different texture than the fourth, and the third tooth being clearly visible while the fourth is not.",
    "), while maintaining consistency with the LR images.",
    "the denoising distribution for fast sampling.",
    "Our approach produces images in just four steps, making it a competitive alternative to the most advanced models that require hundreds or thousands of sampling steps. 2."
  ]
}